  "texts": [
    "This lack of transparency amplifies the risk of LLM-based tools contributing to unequal information exposure for individual users, for instance, due to substantial variation in LLM performance depending on the language of the prompt (e.g.",
    "Therefore, understanding the influence of various factors on LLM performance for detecting information veracity is of particular relevance for academic research and policymakers.In this paper we, therefore, set out to comparatively analyse two popular LLMbased chatbots, ChatGPT and Bing Chat (recently renamed into Microsoft Copilot), in their ability to evaluate the veracity of claims related to different issues which are often targeted with disinformation and are associated with conspiracy theories.",
    "Given that prior research suggests that the performance of different chatbots can vary substantially due to specific settings, we examine how well these chatbots are able to detect accuracy of given statements using AI auditing methodology.",
    "This novel methodology originates from the field of algorithm auditing and comprises systematic evaluation of performance of AI systems in relation to a specific issue or domain [14].",
    "We have chosen the two chatbots that are built on the different versions of the same LLM (GPT 3.5 for ChatGPT and GPT 4 for Bing Chat) as our focus is specifically on the settings and guardrails of the two chatbots and not on the performance of LLMs themselves."
  ]
}